SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 49
BY SENATOR MIZELL
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Recognizes May as National Mental Health Awareness
Month.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To recognize the month of May as Mental Health Awareness Month in Louisiana and to
3 request the residents of this state, organizations, healthcare providers, and
4 government officials to make special efforts to advocate for policies that expand
5 access to high-quality mental health and substance use care that supports Louisiana
6 residents in living longer, healthier, more productive lives.
7 WHEREAS, according to the Louisiana Department of Health, 93% of Louisiana
8 residents live in a Mental Health Professional Shortage Area (MHPSA); and
9 WHEREAS, nearly eight hundred forty thousand adults in Louisiana live with a
10 mental illness and almost sixty thousand adolescents in Louisiana, ages twelve through
11 seventeen, have depression or anxiety; and
12 WHEREAS, 21% of children ages three through seventeen in the United States have
13 been diagnosed with a mental, emotional, or behavioral health condition; and
14 WHEREAS, suicide is the second leading cause of death amongst people ages ten
15 through thirty-four and the eleventh leading cause of death in the United States overall; and
16 WHEREAS, according to the Louisiana Department of Insurance, residents in
17 Louisiana spend the highest percentage of their family income on health insurance, up to
18 15.6%, more than any other state; and
