1 WHEREAS, across the United States, 44% of the people in local jails have a history
2 of mental illness and 63% have a substance use disorder; and
3 WHEREAS, repeated arrests and longer incarceration periods for people with
4 behavioral health issues result in increased human and fiscal costs; and
5 WHEREAS, mental health is essential to a person's life in the same capacity as
6 physical health and allows us to take better care of ourselves and our families; and
7 WHEREAS, maintaining the mental health of a community supports the
8 development of a healthy workforce and advances economic opportunity; and
9 WHEREAS, a lack of access to high-quality mental health and substance use care
10 leads to devastating impacts on the wellbeing of individuals and society; and
11 WHEREAS, Louisiana has made great progress in expanding access to mental health
12 services statewide, but more must be done to reach underserved populations and people in
13 every corner of the state.
14 THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
15 does hereby recognize the month of May as Mental Health Awareness Month in Louisiana
16 and does hereby request residents of this state, organizations, healthcare providers, and
17 government officials to make special efforts to support policies that expand access to high-
18 quality mental health and substance use care and to continue supporting Louisiana residents
19 to live longer, healthier, more productive lives.
